descript.abstract: This theme is a graphic depiction of the legal jurisdictional county perimeters for the State of Oregon.
descript.supplinf: BLM (Bureau of Land Management), CFF (Cartographic Feature File), DLG (Digital Line Graph), DNR (Washington Department of Natural Resources), DRG (Digital Raster Graphic), FIPS (Federal Information Processing Standard), GCD (Geographic Coordinate Database layer), GCDB (Geographic Coordinate Data Base), HYD (WODDB Hydrologic Features layer), LLI (Landlines layer), USFS (U.S. Forest Service), USGS (U.S. Geological Survey), WODDB (Western Oregon Digital Data Base)

sngdate.caldate: REQUIRED: The year (and optionally month, or month and day) for which the data set corresponds to the ground.

idinfo.accconst: Discretionary, contains no sensitive information - generally considered releasable.
idinfo.useconst: None; however, users are reminded that the legal descriptions for County boundaries are published in the Oregon Revised Statutes (ORS 201.010 - 201.370). Any surveys of the county boundaries will be recorded in the counties.

procstep.procdesc: BLM contractor used the cited sources( see source information) to extract the desired line work and create the new coverage. This was accomplished in ARCEDIT using the SELECT & PUT commands. The coverage was then cleaned, built for topology and projected to Lambert Conformal Conic. All line work was ultimately snapped to GCDB points where available.
Coverage reprojected to Geographic projection with a datum of NAD83

citeinfo.title: Geographic Coordinate Database Oregon (Point and Line)

procstep.procdesc: Original coverage version of the county boundary dataset was loaded into the Oregon Washington Corporate SDE instance as two separate feature classes (Line & Polygon). This SDE data is now considered the master version.
Dissolved to create single polygon for each County. This removes the need to separately maintain land/water boundaries within this theme.
Shifted boundary line to match 40 acre land exchange between Coos and Douglas Counties.

dataqual.logic: This theme was built for polygon topology.
dataqual.complete: This theme covers all public and private lands in Oregon.
